---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}, then season all over with salt and
pepper. Place on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Evenly spread @sour cream{2%tbsp} onto tops of chicken, then mound with panko mixture, pressing firmly to adhere (no need to coat underside).

Toss @broccoli florets{8%oz} on opposite side of baking sheet with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast on top rack until chicken is golden brown and cooked through and broccoli is slightly crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If broccoli is finished before chicken, remove from oven and continue roasting chicken.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small, lidded #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup} and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @water{3/4%cup} and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain any excess liquid, if necessary.

Once chicken is done, add @butter{1%tbsp} to couscous; stir until melted. Stir in lemon zest, lemon juice, salt, and pepper to taste. Divide couscous, chicken, and broccoli between plates. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.